# COMPLETE PROGRAM

```python id="ap18"
import pandas as pd
from mlxtend.frequent_patterns import apriori
from mlxtend.frequent_patterns import association_rules

dataset = {
    'Milk': [1, 1, 0, 1, 0],
    'Bread': [1, 1, 1, 0, 1],
    'Butter': [0, 1, 1, 1, 0],
    'Jam': [1, 0, 1, 1, 1]
}

df = pd.DataFrame(dataset)

print("Dataset:")
print(df)

frequent_itemsets = apriori(df, min_support=0.4, use_colnames=True)

print("\nFrequent Itemsets:")
print(frequent_itemsets)

rules = association_rules(frequent_itemsets, metric="confidence", min_threshold=0.7)

print("\nAssociation Rules:")
print(rules)
```

---

# Expected Output

## Frequent Itemsets

* Milk
* Bread
* Jam
* Milk & Bread

---

## Association Rules

Example:

```text id="ap19"
Milk → Bread
```

---

# Important Terms

## Support

Frequency of item occurrence.

Formula:
Support(A)=\frac{Transactions\ containing\ A}{Total\ Transactions}

---

## Confidence

Accuracy of rule.

Formula:
Confidence(A \rightarrow B)=\frac{Support(A\cap B)}{Support(A)}

---

## Lift

Measures relationship strength.

| Lift | Meaning         |
| ---- | --------------- |
| >1   | Strong relation |
| =1   | Independent     |
| <1   | Weak relation   |

